Toast @Sourdough Bread{4%slices} until golden brown in a #toaster{}.

> Toasting bread until golden brown provides the perfect base for the layers.

While bread is toasting, wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @Tomato{1} into rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Core, deseed, and dice half the @Long Green Pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced) into ¼-inch pieces.

> Use the whole pepper if making 4 servings.

Place toasted bread on a clean work surface. Top with half the @Refried Black Beans{8%ounces}.

> Use all @Refried Black Beans{16%ounces} for 4 servings.

Then layer with @Guacamole{1/2%cup}, tomato, green pepper, @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup}, and @Sour Cream{3%tbsp}.

Drizzle with as much @Hot Sauce{1%tsp} as you like.

Divide toasts between plates and serve.